This property is used as the key via which study records can be associated with the appropriate program during data loading, and to identify the correct records during data updates.

A more detailed, multiple sentence description of the program.

An arbitrarily-assigned value used to dictate the order in which programs are displayed within the application's UI.
An acronym or abbreviated form of the title of a broad framework of goals under which related projects or other research activities are grouped. Example - CPTAC

A coded value specifying the kind of algorithm used when reconstructing the image from the data acquired during the acquisition process.
The type of event to which Longitudinal Temporal Offset from Event is relative.
An offset in days from a particular event of significance. May be fractional. In the context of a clinical trial, this is often the days since enrollment, or the baseline imaging Study.

CDEFullName: Image Single Collimation Width 8 Byte Millimeter Number
Description: The width of a single row of acquired data. The units are of linear distance, e.g. mm.

CDEFullName: Image Total Collimation Width 8 Byte Millimeter Number
Description: The width of the total collimation over the area of active x-ray detection. The units are of linear distance, e.g. mm.

CDEFullName: Image Gantry Detector Tilt 16 Character Number
Description: Nominal angle of tilt in degrees of the scanning gantry. The units are of plane angle , e.g. degrees. Zero degrees means the gantry is not tilted, negative degrees are when the top of the gantry is tilted away from where the table enters the gantry.

Ratio of the distance that the table moves during a complete revolution of the source around the gantry orbit, to the width of the total collimation over the area of active x-ray detection. The units are of unity.

CDEFullName: Computed Tomography Dose Index Volume Quantity 8 Byte Number
Description: The average dose over the total volume scanned for the selected CT conditions of operation (calculated according to IEC 60601-2-44, Ed.2.1 (Clause 29.1.103.4)). The units are energy dose, e.g. mGy.

CDEFullName: Imaging Technique CTDI Phantom Type Sequence of Items Text
Description: The type of phantom to use for CTDI measurement according to IEC 60601-2-44
Peak kilovoltage output of the x-ray generator. The units are of electrical potential.
The manner in which tube current is varied in order to limit the dose.
A label describing the mathematical operations used to reconstruct images from the acquired data. The values for this attribute are vendor specific and not coded.

CDEFullName: Imaging Technique Convolution Kernel Group Name
Description: A coded value specifying the family of mathematical operations to use to reconstruct images from the acquired data
The crdc_id is a unique identifier that is generated by CRDC Submission Portal
NonDICOMMRimages identifier

CDEFullName: Image Acquisition Spin-Echo Pulse Sequence Code Category
Description: A coded value specifying an echo category of pulse sequences.

CDEFullName: Imaging Technique MR Diffusion B Value Number
Description: The factor by which the acquisition is sensitized to the Brownian motion of water molecules. The units are of time/area, e.g. s/mm2
A coded value specifying whether diffusion conditions for the frame are directional, or isotropic with respect to direction

CDEFullName: Imaging Technique Magnetic Field Strength Number
Description: A vector quantity indicating the ability of a magnetic field to exert a force on moving electric charges. [The American Heritage Science Dictionary]. The units are of magnetic flux density, e.g. tesla.
A coded value specifying the atomic nucleus that is the target of the acquisition

Acceptable Values: ["DIFFUSION","FLOW_ENCODED_Flow Encoded contrast","FLUID_ATTENUATED_Fluid Attenuated T2 weighted contrast","PERFUSION_Perfusion weighted contrast","PROTON_DENSITY_Proton Density weighted contrast","STIR_Short Tau Inversion Recovery","TAGGING_Superposition of thin saturation bands onto image","T1_T1 weighted contrast","T2_T2 weighted contrast","T2_STAR_T2* weighted contrast","TOF_Time Of Flight weighted contrast"]
Description: A coded value specifying the inherent (as opposed to exogenous) contrast in the acquisition.
Specifies whether an inversion recovery preparatory sequence is used in the acquisition.

CDEFullName: Image Acquisition Pulse Sequence Pulse Sequence Name Text
Description: Name of the pulse sequence that is used for the acquisition. This is usually a vendor-specific name.

CDEFullName: Imaging Technique Multiple Spin Echo Indicator
Description: Specifies whether different lines in k-space are collected for a single frame.
Specifies whether this is a pulse sequence in which the flowing spins are velocity encoded in phase.

CDEFullName: Imaging Technique Time of Flight Contrast Indicator
Description: Specifies whether contrast is created by the inflow of blood in the saturated plane.

CDEFullName: Imaging Technique Arterial Spin Labeling Contrast Name
Description: A coded value specifying how arterial water is used as a diffusable tracer.

CDEFullName: Image Acquisition Steady State Pulse Sequence Type
Description: A coded value specifying how residual transverse magnetization is maintained during the acquisition.

CDEFullName: Image Acquisition Echo Planar Pulse Sequence Indicator
Description: Specifies whether multiple echos of different phase steps are acquired using rephasing gradients instead of repeated 180-degree pulses.
Specifies whether a saturation recovery pulse sequence is used

CDEFullName: Imaging Technique Spectrally Selected Suppression Type
Description: A coded value specifying the type of substance-specific signal suppression is used.

CDEFullName: Imaging Technique Complex Image Component Type
Description: A coded value specifying the channel of the quadrature detected data, or the combination derived from those channels, used to reconstruct the image

CDEFullName: Image Study Admitting Diagnosis Description 64 Character Text
Description: The identified disease(s) or illness(es) at the time of the admission during which imaging was performed.
A coded value specifying the type of equipment that created the images in this imaging study other than that used to acquire the original data.
Specifies whether any images in the study are irreversibly altered during encoding at any time during its life.

CDEFullName: Imaging Study Process Protocol Element Summary Text
Description: A brief statement about the characteristics of this element, which is intended for use by the radiologist, technologist and/or physicist during management of the imaging protocol to understand the characteristics of the element in the protocol.

CDEFullName: Image Study Primary Anatomic Site Sequence of Items Text
Description: A coded value specifying the anatomic location that is the focus of this imaging process protocol element.

CDEFullName: Image Study Spatial Acquisition Type Code
Description: A coded value specifying spatial aspects of the mechanism of data collection.

CDEFullName: Image Study Cardiac Synchronization Technique Code Name
Description: The means used to coordinate the collection or reconstruction of data with the cardiac cycle.

CDEFullName: Image Acquisition Data Collection Location Diameter Number
Description: The diameter of the region over which information is acquired.

CDEFullName: Image Study Respiratory Motion Technique Code Name
Description: The means to be used to coordinate the collection or reconstruction of data with breathing.
A coded value specifying the 3-dimensional spatial orientation of a subject during this imaging acquisition protocol element.

CDEFullName: Imaging Reconstruction Protocol Algorithm Code Text
Description: A coded value specifying the algorithm to use when reconstructing the image from the data acquired during the acquisition process

CDEFullName: Imaging Reconstruction Protocol Field of View Height Number
Description: The vertical dimension of the rectangular region from which data is used in creating the reconstruction of the image.

CDEFullName: Imaging Reconstruction Protocol Field of View Width Number
Description: The horizontal dimension of the rectangular region from which data is used in creating the reconstruction of the image.
The diameter of the region from which data is used in creating the reconstruction of the image.

CDEFullName: Image Plane Slice Thickness Float or Fixed-point Millimeter Number
Description: The cross plane dimension of the reconstructed image.

CDEFullName: Imaging Reconstruction Protocol Reconstruction Interval Millimeter Number
Description: The cross plane distance between the centers of adjacent, parallel reconstructed images.
